WEBVTT

00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:14.973
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:54.763 --> 00:00:55.597
<i>Lee Min-yeong.</i>

00:00:56.181 --> 00:00:57.015
Here.

00:00:58.099 --> 00:00:59.350
Jang Han-seul.

00:01:00.727 --> 00:01:01.644
Jang Han-seul?

00:01:02.562 --> 00:01:03.605
Jang Han-seul.

00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:08.525
Heo Do-jun.

00:01:08.526 --> 00:01:09.486
Here.

00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:17.117
I reviewed your last assignments and left them over there.

00:01:17.118 --> 00:01:19.369
Make sure to collect them after class.

00:01:19.370 --> 00:01:20.497
Yes, Professor.

00:01:21.623 --> 00:01:22.749
Did you take notes?

00:01:24.417 --> 00:01:27.462
- Can you lend them to me next time? - I'll send them to you.

00:01:32.592 --> 00:01:34.719
Professor!

00:01:37.639 --> 00:01:39.140
This...

00:01:40.391 --> 00:01:43.852
I mean, "trash"? How could you write something like this?

00:01:43.853 --> 00:01:45.855
You should know, sir,

00:01:46.356 --> 00:01:48.358
That I'm an influencer.

00:01:49.317 --> 00:01:51.694
Do you even know what that means?

00:01:52.737 --> 00:01:55.782
My blog alone has over 30,000 subscribers.

00:01:56.491 --> 00:01:58.284
Do you know how many likes I get a day?

00:01:58.785 --> 00:01:59.661
Is that right?

00:02:00.537 --> 00:02:02.080
How impressive.

00:02:02.622 --> 00:02:04.414
Then that blog must be a trash can.

00:02:04.415 --> 00:02:05.457
On second thought,

00:02:05.458 --> 00:02:08.670
If it's full of writing like this, a "landfill" might be more fitting.

00:02:12.632 --> 00:02:14.175
Twelve paragraphs

00:02:14.759 --> 00:02:17.011
And 167 sentences.

00:02:17.512 --> 00:02:20.682
You may consider this writing since you filled the pages with whatever,

00:02:21.182 --> 00:02:24.519
But unfortunately, these pages don't hold a single true sentence.

00:02:25.270 --> 00:02:28.523
Not a single sentence that comes from the heart and rings true.

00:02:29.482 --> 00:02:32.401
It's just a plethora of clichés, cheap sentimentality,

00:02:32.402 --> 00:02:35.905
And sentences copied and pasted from other people's work.

00:02:36.781 --> 00:02:38.615
How else should I describe these words

00:02:38.616 --> 00:02:41.744
You've simply regurgitated without grasping their meaning?

00:02:42.495 --> 00:02:45.582
If you can think of a more fitting term than "trash," let me know.

00:02:48.293 --> 00:02:51.004
Then, going forward, I'll try to use that word.

00:02:57.719 --> 00:02:58.928
Are we done here?

00:03:04.309 --> 00:03:05.226
What an asshole.

00:03:05.727 --> 00:03:09.271
I could just strangle him. That soul-crushing bastard.

00:03:09.272 --> 00:03:11.232
If only his class was optional.

00:03:12.901 --> 00:03:15.361
I heard he acts like that because he's insecure.

00:03:17.488 --> 00:03:19.657
<i>Our seniors told me over drinks one time.</i>

00:03:20.325 --> 00:03:22.327
<i>Heo Mun-oh has only written one novel.</i>

00:03:22.827 --> 00:03:24.495
<i>Over 20 years ago, at that.</i>

00:03:24.996 --> 00:03:28.041
<i>But he hasn't been able to write a second novel since.</i>

00:03:28.541 --> 00:03:31.376
<i>He wants to, but he can't, no matter how hard he fucking tries.</i>

00:03:31.377 --> 00:03:35.590
<i>So he takes his inferiority complex and stress out on his students.</i>

00:03:36.299 --> 00:03:37.383
<i>Total loser.</i>

00:03:37.967 --> 00:03:39.510
RESEARCH IN PROGRESS DO NOT DISTURB

00:03:40.845 --> 00:03:41.763
Mun-oh, you're here.

00:03:43.389 --> 00:03:44.933
The door was unlocked, so...

00:03:48.311 --> 00:03:51.063
Professor Park, didn't we see each other yesterday?

00:03:51.064 --> 00:03:54.524
Well, that was yesterday, Mun-oh. I came because I wanted to see you <i>today</i>.

00:03:54.525 --> 00:03:57.653
Calling me Mun-oh again. I told you to stop using my name.

00:03:57.654 --> 00:03:59.030
Yes, Professor Heo.

00:04:00.114 --> 00:04:02.784
But I like calling you by name.

00:04:03.701 --> 00:04:05.410
Did you get home safe yesterday?

00:04:05.411 --> 00:04:08.414
- Want some coffee? - No, I just had some.

00:04:09.123 --> 00:04:11.333
Goodness, what is this?

00:04:11.334 --> 00:04:12.918
You're so stubborn, Mun-oh.

00:04:12.919 --> 00:04:15.838
Do you still take attendance by hand?

00:04:16.839 --> 00:04:19.591
Shall I install the software for you? It's so much easier.

00:04:19.592 --> 00:04:21.260
No, thank you.

00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:23.179
I like doing things my way.

00:04:24.013 --> 00:04:25.098
What brings you here?

00:04:25.598 --> 00:04:28.308
You must've come all the way from Engineering for a reason.

00:04:28.309 --> 00:04:32.522
Well, I wanted to speak to you about this yesterday, but I forgot.

00:04:33.022 --> 00:04:34.148
Mun-oh,

00:04:34.732 --> 00:04:38.319
I heard you know the author Kim Su-hun.

00:04:41.614 --> 00:04:42.448
Who?

00:04:43.032 --> 00:04:43.865
Kim Su-hun?

00:04:43.866 --> 00:04:46.411
Yes. I heard you were classmates back in university.

00:04:47.203 --> 00:04:50.622
I had no idea you had such impressive connections.

00:04:50.623 --> 00:04:52.249
Had I known that from the start,

00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:54.835
I would have asked you to introduce us earlier.

00:04:54.836 --> 00:04:56.004
What do you mean?

00:04:56.504 --> 00:04:59.716
I believe I told you about this previously.

00:05:00.216 --> 00:05:04.511
I organize the School of Engineering's monthly cultural events.

00:05:04.512 --> 00:05:07.556
Our students are emotionally stunted, so I thought--

00:05:07.557 --> 00:05:08.849
Just get to the point.

00:05:08.850 --> 00:05:10.727
Right, yes. The point.

00:05:11.477 --> 00:05:15.230
The point is, we're in talks to invite Kim Su-hun next month.

00:05:15.231 --> 00:05:19.693
To give a lecture on his new novel and have a discussion afterward.

00:05:19.694 --> 00:05:23.072
I was hoping you could host that discussion.

00:05:26.659 --> 00:05:27.493
Well?

00:05:30.747 --> 00:05:32.873
- You want me to host the discussion? - Yes.

00:05:32.874 --> 00:05:35.543
Mr. Kim was the one who suggested you first.

00:05:40.423 --> 00:05:42.257
Kim Su-hun suggested me?

00:05:42.258 --> 00:05:43.634
Yes.

00:05:44.218 --> 00:05:45.427
What did he say?

00:05:45.428 --> 00:05:49.098
Just that he would feel more at ease, and it'd be fun to chat with a friend.

00:05:49.807 --> 00:05:51.434
He said he'd come if you did it.

00:05:57.607 --> 00:05:59.108
Kim Su-hun said that?

00:06:00.276 --> 00:06:01.110
Yes.

00:06:07.617 --> 00:06:10.327
- Road's slippery. Careful. - Can we expect a great article?

00:06:10.328 --> 00:06:14.456
Don't worry, sir. Just be ready to print more copies of the book.

00:06:14.457 --> 00:06:15.458
Su-hun.

00:06:19.504 --> 00:06:21.839
Mun-oh! Hey, just a second.

00:06:22.340 --> 00:06:23.299
Mr. Gu?

00:06:23.883 --> 00:06:26.511
Please go ahead. I'll be right there.

00:06:27.011 --> 00:06:30.138
- Okay, sure. - Hurry. The real interview starts now.

00:06:30.139 --> 00:06:31.057
Right.

00:06:31.557 --> 00:06:33.810
- Join us at the pork rind joint. - You got it.

00:06:36.396 --> 00:06:40.066
I should have given you a call first. Sorry about that.

00:06:40.566 --> 00:06:44.278
Weren't we supposed to have dinner together today?

00:06:45.071 --> 00:06:46.530
That's what I thought.

00:06:46.531 --> 00:06:48.658
Yeah, I was thinking the same.

00:06:49.409 --> 00:06:50.867
And I have something to say.

00:06:50.868 --> 00:06:53.996
But Mr. Gu suddenly decided to join us.

00:06:54.580 --> 00:06:55.664
You know Mr. Gu, right?

00:06:55.665 --> 00:06:58.459
Of course. What writer doesn't know Gu Yeong-ho?

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:00.586
First time seeing him in person.

00:07:02.797 --> 00:07:03.631
So,

00:07:04.841 --> 00:07:06.134
What did you have to say?

00:07:06.634 --> 00:07:07.718
What is it?

00:07:09.762 --> 00:07:12.932
Is it about what I asked you a while ago?

00:07:13.724 --> 00:07:14.559
That favor?

00:07:16.644 --> 00:07:17.520
Yeah.

00:07:20.481 --> 00:07:22.024
I don't think I can endorse you.

00:07:23.192 --> 00:07:26.112
I think I've been too liberal with writing endorsements lately.

00:07:28.823 --> 00:07:30.908
Liberal?

00:07:32.493 --> 00:07:35.370
Did you even read my manuscript?

00:07:35.371 --> 00:07:36.831
Of course I did.

00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:40.542
But let's talk about that later, okay?

00:07:40.543 --> 00:07:41.669
No, hey, Su-hun.

00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:43.921
Tell me now.

00:07:44.422 --> 00:07:46.507
What did you think? Just tell me.

00:08:49.737 --> 00:08:53.741
I couldn't really tell what the author was trying to say.

00:08:54.909 --> 00:08:56.619
It made me think,

00:08:57.119 --> 00:08:59.622
Why bother writing when you have nothing to say?

00:09:01.707 --> 00:09:03.709
It's okay to live as is.

00:09:05.211 --> 00:09:07.463
But, above all else,

00:09:08.506 --> 00:09:10.550
You should relearn sentence structures.

00:09:25.439 --> 00:09:27.733
<i>That's why writing the first sentence is crucial.</i>

00:09:31.779 --> 00:09:33.656
The moment the first sentence is written,

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:38.286
The author finally takes their first step into their story.

00:09:41.956 --> 00:09:43.374
Listen to this sentence.

00:09:45.585 --> 00:09:50.423
"How happy I am that I am gone!"

00:09:52.758 --> 00:09:53.759
"My dear friend,

00:09:55.344 --> 00:09:57.888
What a thing is the heart of man!"

00:09:59.056 --> 00:10:01.267
Anyone know which novel's first sentence this is?

00:10:05.521 --> 00:10:06.355
No one?

00:10:12.069 --> 00:10:15.531
This is the quintessential classic. Goethe's--

00:10:19.577 --> 00:10:20.453
Who was that?

00:10:22.663 --> 00:10:23.873
What was that noise?

00:10:27.084 --> 00:10:28.252
Apologies.

00:10:35.259 --> 00:10:39.096
That was the first sentence of Goethe's <i>The Sorrows of Young Werther</i>.

00:10:40.014 --> 00:10:41.140
As you all will know,

00:10:41.724 --> 00:10:45.852
It's written in the form of letters sent by Werther to his friend Albert...

00:10:45.853 --> 00:10:47.605
Are my classes a joke to you?

00:10:51.901 --> 00:10:53.235
Am I a joke to you?

00:10:56.656 --> 00:10:57.490
Get up.

00:10:58.532 --> 00:10:59.784
Get up.

00:11:01.702 --> 00:11:02.620
You won't?

00:11:04.080 --> 00:11:05.206
Get out!

00:11:07.833 --> 00:11:08.917
Out of my class.

00:11:08.918 --> 00:11:12.088
It's not Albert, it's Wilhelm.

00:11:16.133 --> 00:11:17.051
What?

00:11:18.302 --> 00:11:20.680
Werther's friend is Wilhelm.

00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:26.227
Albert is the fiancé of Lotte, the woman Werther loves.

00:11:30.815 --> 00:11:32.817
The object of Werther's jealousy,

00:11:33.651 --> 00:11:36.487
Admiration, and inferiority complex.

00:11:37.988 --> 00:11:38.948
But,

00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:43.619
In the sense that all of those things are part of friendship,

00:11:44.912 --> 00:11:47.164
I guess you could say they were friends.

00:11:48.749 --> 00:11:50.459
The object of his envy,

00:11:52.002 --> 00:11:53.295
And yet, his friend.

00:11:59.385 --> 00:12:02.263
Time's up, Professor.

00:12:07.935 --> 00:12:09.103
Class dismissed.

00:12:15.276 --> 00:12:16.360
Hey, get up.

00:12:33.043 --> 00:12:35.295
FUNDAMENTALS OF WRITING CONCEPTS AND PRACTICES

00:12:35.296 --> 00:12:36.337
PROFESSOR HEO MUN-OH

00:12:36.338 --> 00:12:37.922
ELECTRONICS ENGINEERING LEE KANG

00:12:37.923 --> 00:12:39.341
Hey, thank you.

00:12:39.842 --> 00:12:42.052
You saved me. I almost got cooked.

00:12:42.845 --> 00:12:44.930
I'll treat you to a nice meal today.

00:12:45.431 --> 00:12:46.307
What do you want?

00:12:46.807 --> 00:12:49.185
Whatever you want. Fried chicken, pizza...

00:12:49.852 --> 00:12:53.314
<i>But, if jealousy preceded any affection,</i>

00:12:53.814 --> 00:12:56.901
<i>could that relationship still be called a friendship?</i>

00:13:00.529 --> 00:13:03.990
<i>I first met Se-yun in the winter before we started school.</i>

00:13:03.991 --> 00:13:04.909
<i>A mere</i>

00:13:05.493 --> 00:13:06.494
<i>coincidence.</i>

00:13:14.502 --> 00:13:16.420
Hurry up and clear the table.

00:13:17.922 --> 00:13:19.340
Wait, this...

00:13:32.436 --> 00:13:33.854
I held onto this for you.

00:13:34.355 --> 00:13:36.148
Thank you.

00:13:37.775 --> 00:13:39.193
I found it.

00:13:57.628 --> 00:13:58.838
Thank you so much.

00:13:59.588 --> 00:14:00.714
Thank you.

00:14:03.551 --> 00:14:06.262
<i>Our meeting was a coincidence, but us becoming friends</i>

00:14:06.971 --> 00:14:08.222
<i>wasn't a coincidence.</i>

00:14:09.014 --> 00:14:10.181
<i>I planned it.</i>

00:14:10.182 --> 00:14:11.392
CODING CLUB

00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:20.484
Are you in YDOC too?

00:14:20.985 --> 00:14:22.653
They gave these as freshmen goodies.

00:14:25.781 --> 00:14:28.742
I'm Kim Se-yun, class of '25. Library and Information Science. You?

00:14:29.243 --> 00:14:31.495
Lee Kang, class of '25. Electronics Engineering.

00:14:33.080 --> 00:14:34.789
An engineer taking this class?

00:14:34.790 --> 00:14:36.625
Then again, it is a required course.

00:14:40.754 --> 00:14:42.506
So do you know how to code?

00:14:43.007 --> 00:14:45.926
Honestly, I'm clueless. I joined because I like video games.

00:14:50.014 --> 00:14:51.557
Coding isn't that hard.

00:14:52.349 --> 00:14:53.350
It's easy.

00:14:54.059 --> 00:14:54.894
Really?

00:14:58.355 --> 00:15:00.316
Wow, how do you do this?

00:15:01.150 --> 00:15:02.067
Teach me.

00:15:02.776 --> 00:15:05.362
Not now. I have to go to my part-time job.

00:15:07.448 --> 00:15:09.533
How about tomorrow? Want to come to my place?

00:15:10.492 --> 00:15:12.202
<i>My plan worked.</i>

00:15:12.703 --> 00:15:13.912
- Your place? - Yeah.

00:15:13.913 --> 00:15:16.165
<i>I finally became friends with Se-yun.</i>

00:15:16.665 --> 00:15:19.083
<i>Friendly enough to invite each other over.</i>

00:15:19.084 --> 00:15:20.878
TO BE CONTINUED...

00:16:10.302 --> 00:16:14.848
<i>Is it possible to feel nostalgia for a place you've never been to?</i>

00:16:17.601 --> 00:16:19.979
<i>Is it possible to be filled with longing</i>

00:16:20.729 --> 00:16:22.731
<i>for someone you've never met?</i>

00:16:31.240 --> 00:16:33.784
<i>It was my first time at his house, but it felt familiar.</i>

00:16:34.702 --> 00:16:36.996
<i>It looked just like it did in the photo.</i>

00:16:39.498 --> 00:16:40.958
Come this way.

00:16:45.879 --> 00:16:46.797
Mom.

00:16:49.550 --> 00:16:51.093
Oh, you're home.

00:16:51.593 --> 00:16:54.096
This is my friend from my university club.

00:16:55.139 --> 00:16:56.598
I mentioned him, didn't I?

00:16:58.350 --> 00:17:00.019
Right, it's you.

00:17:01.061 --> 00:17:02.396
Nice to meet you.

00:17:02.938 --> 00:17:03.814
I'm Lee Kang.

00:17:05.733 --> 00:17:07.317
<i>No, different from the photo.</i>

00:17:07.901 --> 00:17:10.112
<i>They were far more beautiful than I'd expected.</i>

00:17:10.612 --> 00:17:11.446
<i>The house.</i>

00:17:11.447 --> 00:17:12.613
- So good. - Right?

00:17:12.614 --> 00:17:13.532
<i>And the person.</i>

00:17:14.533 --> 00:17:16.159
I think I'm gifted.

00:17:16.160 --> 00:17:17.494
Good job.

00:17:18.245 --> 00:17:19.288
As you should.

00:17:54.698 --> 00:17:56.075
"To be continued.."

00:17:56.575 --> 00:17:59.660
Oh my. What is this? Who wrote this?

00:17:59.661 --> 00:18:00.746
Some kid.

00:18:01.914 --> 00:18:02.998
What do you think?

00:18:04.249 --> 00:18:05.542
I'm not sure.

00:18:07.086 --> 00:18:09.963
So he purposefully approached and befriended this boy?

00:18:11.340 --> 00:18:12.424
No, that's not it.

00:18:12.925 --> 00:18:16.344
He pretended to be his friend so he could go to his house?

00:18:16.345 --> 00:18:20.932
My goodness. What does this kid want? Why would he write something like this?

00:18:20.933 --> 00:18:22.558
For God's sake.

00:18:22.559 --> 00:18:23.810
What the heck?

00:18:23.811 --> 00:18:27.648
I asked for your thoughts as an expert, yet you're saying the same thing I did.

00:18:28.273 --> 00:18:30.442
What's he thinking? You're the therapist.

00:18:31.485 --> 00:18:34.321
Well, it's too early to make any judgments based on this.

00:18:36.990 --> 00:18:39.535
His mental state doesn't seem so complex.

00:18:40.786 --> 00:18:41.662
He's envious.

00:18:42.621 --> 00:18:45.957
He must have seen something he desperately wanted in that other kid.

00:18:45.958 --> 00:18:50.546
And since he can't do anything about it, he's venting through writing. Imagination.

00:18:53.674 --> 00:18:55.550
While it's a bit peculiar,

00:18:55.551 --> 00:18:58.428
Being able to express these feelings is a good thing.

00:19:01.682 --> 00:19:03.475
I'm curious what he'll write next.

00:19:04.059 --> 00:19:05.477
He's a decent writer too.

00:19:07.104 --> 00:19:08.105
Isn't it a first

00:19:08.605 --> 00:19:10.232
For you to have such a student?

00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:14.444
Yes, it is.

00:19:15.737 --> 00:19:17.739
Are you going to take him under your wing?

00:19:18.240 --> 00:19:19.658
Don't be ridiculous.

00:19:20.159 --> 00:19:20.993
I'm going.

00:19:21.743 --> 00:19:22.995
Do you know...

00:19:26.790 --> 00:19:29.042
How long it's been since you came into my room?

00:19:29.543 --> 00:19:30.377
Do you remember?

00:19:34.006 --> 00:19:35.007
Good night.

00:20:00.157 --> 00:20:02.367
<i>I'm curious what he'll write next.</i>

00:20:03.493 --> 00:20:06.038
<i>Isn't it a first for you to have such a student?</i>

00:20:07.497 --> 00:20:09.541
<i>Are you going to take him under your wing?</i>

00:20:34.775 --> 00:20:36.652
Why did you ask me to stay behind?

00:20:37.861 --> 00:20:39.238
Did you have something

00:20:40.614 --> 00:20:41.531
To say?

00:20:44.076 --> 00:20:46.620
You humiliated me in front of the class last time.

00:20:47.537 --> 00:20:48.664
Did it feel good?

00:21:05.722 --> 00:21:07.391
Is that Kim Se-yun?

00:21:09.810 --> 00:21:10.644
Yes.

00:21:11.728 --> 00:21:14.231
Does he know what your assignment is about?

00:21:14.731 --> 00:21:15.899
Have you shown it to him?

00:21:17.192 --> 00:21:18.026
No.

00:21:18.902 --> 00:21:21.280
I thought only you read the assignments, Professor.

00:21:22.114 --> 00:21:23.615
You said that in the first class.

00:21:28.662 --> 00:21:29.538
Sit.

00:21:48.348 --> 00:21:49.266
What is it...

00:21:51.393 --> 00:21:53.020
That you want to write about?

00:21:53.812 --> 00:21:55.188
What are you trying to write?

00:21:56.148 --> 00:21:57.190
What do you mean?

00:21:57.691 --> 00:22:00.569
It's an assignment, so I just wrote whatever I felt like.

00:22:01.153 --> 00:22:01.987
As you told us to.

00:22:02.988 --> 00:22:04.323
No.

00:22:06.575 --> 00:22:09.411
You know what I'm asking you.

00:22:10.829 --> 00:22:12.164
Let's not play dumb.

00:22:22.841 --> 00:22:23.967
You...

00:22:26.928 --> 00:22:28.430
Envy Kim Se-yun, don't you?

00:22:30.057 --> 00:22:31.683
And you want to be him?

00:22:33.352 --> 00:22:35.562
That's why you wrote this, isn't it?

00:22:40.734 --> 00:22:41.943
But you know,

00:22:43.528 --> 00:22:45.280
In Kim Se-yun's assignment,

00:22:45.822 --> 00:22:47.741
There's not a single word about you.

00:22:48.617 --> 00:22:50.701
He doesn't seem to care at all

00:22:50.702 --> 00:22:52.996
Whether you envy him or not.

00:22:53.955 --> 00:22:55.624
You're the only one who's suffering.

00:23:00.212 --> 00:23:01.671
Do you know it too?

00:23:03.715 --> 00:23:04.800
That feeling?

00:23:15.394 --> 00:23:19.106
So are you suggesting that I should write about something else?

00:23:21.066 --> 00:23:25.069
- There's nothing else I want to write. - No, write. Write about this.

00:23:25.070 --> 00:23:28.322
My point is that you should keep writing.

00:23:28.323 --> 00:23:30.158
Even if it's hard, just write.

00:23:31.576 --> 00:23:33.620
What's important is wanting to write.

00:23:37.749 --> 00:23:38.834
You have talent.

00:23:43.630 --> 00:23:44.506
And

00:23:45.632 --> 00:23:48.468
Take one-on-one literature lessons from me. Once a week.

00:23:49.261 --> 00:23:50.553
- One-on-one? - Yes.

00:23:50.554 --> 00:23:51.763
One-on-one.

00:23:54.182 --> 00:23:56.308
I'm saying I'll make time for you.

00:23:56.309 --> 00:23:57.685
What? Don't you get it?

00:23:57.686 --> 00:23:59.104
No, I don't think I can.

00:24:00.856 --> 00:24:02.482
I have several part-time jobs.

00:24:05.193 --> 00:24:06.903
And money matters more to me.

00:24:16.413 --> 00:24:17.289
Then,

00:24:18.707 --> 00:24:22.169
What if I pay you as much as you earn from one of your part-time jobs?

00:24:30.135 --> 00:24:30.969
Why?

00:24:34.181 --> 00:24:35.056
Do you like me?

00:24:39.186 --> 00:24:41.563
Crazy bastard. You're talking nonsense.

00:24:50.197 --> 00:24:51.031
Lee Kang.

00:24:54.159 --> 00:24:57.704
Quit talking nonsense, you punk, and listen to me carefully.

00:24:59.873 --> 00:25:02.167
<i>You can't be Kim Se-yun,</i>

00:25:02.709 --> 00:25:06.379
<i>but you can write as much as you want about your desire to become him.</i>

00:25:07.839 --> 00:25:10.050
<i>As long as you can sublimate that feeling.</i>

00:25:10.717 --> 00:25:13.428
<i>That's what literature is. That's the power of literature.</i>

00:25:16.515 --> 00:25:18.057
<i>I want to help you</i>

00:25:18.058 --> 00:25:21.895
<i>so that the things you write don't end up as mere scribbles</i>

00:25:22.812 --> 00:25:24.523
<i>but become a coherent story.</i>

00:25:26.733 --> 00:25:27.567
<i>Because</i>

00:25:28.068 --> 00:25:30.195
Talent is a rare thing,

00:25:30.862 --> 00:25:32.489
And I'm your teacher.

00:25:34.449 --> 00:25:37.911
<i>All right, Professor. I'll quit one of my part-time jobs.</i>

00:25:44.251 --> 00:25:51.049
ALL RIGHT, TEACHER I'LL QUIT ONE OF MY PART-TIME JOBS

00:26:32.090 --> 00:26:33.091
Why are you grinning?

00:26:34.342 --> 00:26:35.927
I just find it funny.

00:26:36.761 --> 00:26:40.056
Literature lessons? I didn't think you'd actually do it.

00:26:41.766 --> 00:26:44.560
Anyway, it's nice to see you in good spirits.

00:26:44.561 --> 00:26:47.522
Didn't you say you were running late for your appointment?

00:26:48.023 --> 00:26:49.107
You should get going.

00:26:51.151 --> 00:26:53.777
Still, I don't quite like you doing the lessons here.

00:26:53.778 --> 00:26:57.115
Why at home? You could do them on campus or at a café.

00:26:58.283 --> 00:27:02.537
I told you, if we do them outside, people will see us and start talking.

00:27:04.331 --> 00:27:08.209
And when you meet Professor Park and Seong-hui, you can't tell them, okay?

00:27:08.710 --> 00:27:09.543
Say I was busy.

00:27:09.544 --> 00:27:13.173
Oh, all right. Why do you always insist on being so secretive?

00:27:15.508 --> 00:27:17.301
I'm off. Enjoy your lesson.

00:27:17.302 --> 00:27:18.428
Sure.

00:28:17.404 --> 00:28:18.238
Hey.

00:28:19.906 --> 00:28:20.740
Come on in.

00:28:33.586 --> 00:28:34.462
This way.

00:28:42.429 --> 00:28:43.930
Why aren't you coming in?

00:28:55.692 --> 00:28:58.278
Why do you look so down? You're here to study.

00:28:58.820 --> 00:29:00.780
You haven't even greeted me properly.

00:29:02.782 --> 00:29:03.992
I did say hi.

00:29:04.909 --> 00:29:06.661
You little... Sit.

00:29:09.080 --> 00:29:09.914
Actually...

00:29:13.084 --> 00:29:16.504
Something's been weighing on me, and I thought I'd tell you over the phone,

00:29:17.005 --> 00:29:19.716
But I figured I should tell you in person.

00:29:21.676 --> 00:29:22.761
What do you mean?

00:29:25.221 --> 00:29:26.848
I can't take these lessons.

00:29:29.350 --> 00:29:30.185
The thing is,

00:29:31.019 --> 00:29:33.645
Something happened when I was at Se-yun's place yesterday.

00:29:33.646 --> 00:29:37.317
I might not be able to go there again, which means I won't be able to write.

00:29:37.859 --> 00:29:39.861
Then these classes would be pointless, so...

00:29:41.905 --> 00:29:42.739
Wait.

00:29:43.740 --> 00:29:46.618
Take your time and explain. Why, what happened?

00:29:52.832 --> 00:29:55.210
Do you remember I wrote about the coding club?

00:29:55.919 --> 00:29:56.753
Yeah.

00:29:57.462 --> 00:30:00.006
Our club has a competition coming up in two weeks.

00:30:00.507 --> 00:30:02.926
The preliminaries of a national tournament for clubs.

00:30:06.429 --> 00:30:08.973
Se-yun and I were going to enter as a team,

00:30:09.474 --> 00:30:12.685
So I went over to his place yesterday to study together, but...

00:30:13.269 --> 00:30:14.103
But?

00:30:14.938 --> 00:30:16.313
Try up to this page.

00:30:16.314 --> 00:30:17.232
Okay.

00:30:18.358 --> 00:30:20.985
- I'm going to the bathroom. - Sure, go ahead.

00:30:57.438 --> 00:30:59.399
<i>I was only going to the bathroom,</i>

00:30:59.899 --> 00:31:01.693
<i>but I suddenly got curious.</i>

00:31:21.170 --> 00:31:24.132
<i>Frankly, it was wrong of me.</i>

00:32:54.138 --> 00:32:55.264
I'm sorry.

00:32:56.599 --> 00:32:58.309
I couldn't find the bathroom.

00:33:00.269 --> 00:33:03.689
I see. I thought you were my Yun.

00:33:03.690 --> 00:33:05.565
There's also a bathroom upstairs.

00:33:05.566 --> 00:33:07.819
And one for guests by the front door.

00:33:09.362 --> 00:33:11.197
Yes, understood.

00:33:12.031 --> 00:33:13.574
I'll use one of those from now on.

00:33:19.122 --> 00:33:22.417
<i>Even though I was out of line, Se-yun's mom was kind.</i>

00:33:22.917 --> 00:33:25.712
<i>She didn't get mad, was considerate and gracious,</i>

00:33:26.212 --> 00:33:28.172
<i>and didn't seem upset during dinner, either.</i>

00:33:28.673 --> 00:33:30.508
- It's hot. - Okay.

00:33:33.928 --> 00:33:35.680
What's taking you so long? Come on.

00:33:36.180 --> 00:33:38.099
The kids are hungry and waiting.

00:33:38.599 --> 00:33:40.184
Yes, be right there.

00:33:47.984 --> 00:33:52.822
So you're Se-yun's new friend. Nice to meet you. Lee Kang, right?

00:33:54.073 --> 00:33:54.906
Hello.

00:33:54.907 --> 00:33:55.867
Have a seat.

00:33:59.871 --> 00:34:01.789
I hear you're great with computers.

00:34:02.623 --> 00:34:05.126
You're all Se-yun talks about these days.

00:34:06.210 --> 00:34:07.462
It's true.

00:34:08.421 --> 00:34:10.589
He's had so many friends but never like this.

00:34:10.590 --> 00:34:12.591
I don't talk about him that much.

00:34:12.592 --> 00:34:16.888
The truth is, I'm only able to enter this competition thanks to Kang.

00:34:17.388 --> 00:34:19.974
Even all the seniors are floored by his skills.

00:34:21.017 --> 00:34:22.976
Hey, why are you exaggerating?

00:34:22.977 --> 00:34:23.936
Exaggerating?

00:34:24.520 --> 00:34:26.647
Anyway, please take good care of Se-yun.

00:34:27.148 --> 00:34:30.234
His dream is to become a programmer now, all of a sudden.

00:34:31.319 --> 00:34:33.821
Had we known, we'd have made him study engineering.

00:34:35.031 --> 00:34:36.240
Okay. Let's eat.

00:34:38.201 --> 00:34:39.202
Let's say grace first.

00:34:39.702 --> 00:34:42.871
In the name of the Father, of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit. Amen.

00:34:42.872 --> 00:34:45.874
Bless us, O Lord, and these gifts, which we are about to receive

00:34:45.875 --> 00:34:47.626
From thy bounty...

00:34:47.627 --> 00:34:51.172
<i>But, as I was about to head home, I found out the truth.</i>

00:34:51.672 --> 00:34:53.340
<i>How she really felt about me.</i>

00:34:53.341 --> 00:34:57.178
I don't know. There's something suspicious and sneaky about him.

00:34:57.845 --> 00:35:00.306
You know how everyone gives off a vibe.

00:35:00.807 --> 00:35:04.936
I felt it from the first time I met him. I wish he'd stop coming over.

00:35:06.229 --> 00:35:07.271
What is it now?

00:35:09.732 --> 00:35:11.609
What's got you all worked up this time?

00:35:13.903 --> 00:35:16.614
We can't exactly ban a friend who Se-yun likes.

00:35:17.115 --> 00:35:19.117
All we can do is just watch over him.

00:35:20.368 --> 00:35:23.663
Do you know what happened earlier today? He was in our bedroom...

00:35:25.706 --> 00:35:30.253
I'm just saying I'd prefer our Yun to be friends with someone

00:35:30.795 --> 00:35:32.547
More cheerful and lively.

00:35:33.297 --> 00:35:34.465
Seriously?

00:35:35.550 --> 00:35:38.094
I thought the kid was fine. Seemed smart.

00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:42.932
Well then, let's at least leave them be until after the competition.

00:35:43.683 --> 00:35:45.101
What if they win an award?

00:35:46.477 --> 00:35:50.690
They say awards at competitions like that stand out on job applications.

00:35:51.190 --> 00:35:53.609
That's been on my mind too.

00:35:54.402 --> 00:35:55.486
All right.

00:35:55.987 --> 00:35:58.322
If it means it's going to help our son.

00:35:59.073 --> 00:36:01.492
- Let's revisit this after the competition. - Yeah.

00:36:13.671 --> 00:36:15.839
What'd you do that for, huh?

00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:17.758
I know what I did was wrong.

00:36:20.094 --> 00:36:22.805
So, are you telling me

00:36:24.223 --> 00:36:27.560
That you have to win that competition or whatever it's called

00:36:28.060 --> 00:36:30.271
In order to keep going over to his place?

00:36:30.855 --> 00:36:32.815
Yes. That's how it is.

00:36:33.399 --> 00:36:36.652
Then win it. Just do it. You're good at programming, aren't you?

00:36:37.153 --> 00:36:38.862
Don't talk about what you don't know.

00:36:38.863 --> 00:36:41.449
I may be better than Se-yun, but I don't stand a chance.

00:36:46.495 --> 00:36:47.788
Hey, but it's not like

00:36:48.331 --> 00:36:51.417
You have to go inside that house in order to be able to write.

00:36:53.502 --> 00:36:56.296
What would I feel or write about if I don't?

00:36:56.297 --> 00:36:57.590
That was my inspiration.

00:36:59.634 --> 00:37:00.635
You're right.

00:37:01.344 --> 00:37:02.470
Yes, that's true.

00:37:03.638 --> 00:37:04.472
That's true.

00:37:07.141 --> 00:37:08.517
Then what should we do?

00:37:09.101 --> 00:37:12.813
We need to come up with a good idea...

00:37:14.732 --> 00:37:16.984
There might be a way, but...

00:37:19.111 --> 00:37:19.946
What is it?

00:37:28.788 --> 00:37:31.749
Forget it. You couldn't do it, Mr. Heo.

00:37:32.250 --> 00:37:35.670
What are you talking about, punk? What couldn't I do? Tell me.

00:37:43.886 --> 00:37:45.054
The competition problems.

00:37:46.597 --> 00:37:47.723
Competition problems?

00:37:51.185 --> 00:37:52.311
What about them?

00:38:07.368 --> 00:38:08.452
You don't mean...

00:38:11.414 --> 00:38:13.374
You're not asking me...

00:38:15.167 --> 00:38:16.627
To steal the competition problems...

00:38:18.921 --> 00:38:19.964
Are you?

00:38:21.757 --> 00:38:24.051
I can't think of any other way out of this.

00:38:29.307 --> 00:38:30.433
Are you crazy?

00:38:32.935 --> 00:38:34.228
You're a lunatic.

00:38:38.733 --> 00:38:39.817
You little punk.

00:38:41.444 --> 00:38:44.739
I'm your teacher and a professor at that school!

00:38:45.406 --> 00:38:47.700
How dare you ask such a thing!

00:38:52.163 --> 00:38:53.581
Hey, get out.

00:38:54.623 --> 00:38:57.752
Get out of here! I'm not interested in giving you lessons anymore.

00:38:58.336 --> 00:39:00.463
You're a real piece of work, aren't you?

00:39:02.340 --> 00:39:03.424
Get out!

00:39:07.803 --> 00:39:09.263
Then it can't be helped.

00:39:11.057 --> 00:39:13.017
I'll just forget about your teaching offer.

00:39:22.151 --> 00:39:23.569
Why, that punk...

00:39:25.363 --> 00:39:27.531
What the hell is wrong with him?

00:39:40.419 --> 00:39:42.463
Why didn't you hand in your assignment?

00:39:43.214 --> 00:39:44.924
I had nothing to write about.

00:39:53.307 --> 00:39:54.183
Hey, Lee Kang!

00:39:55.393 --> 00:39:59.313
Are you really not handing something in? At this rate, I won't help you...

00:40:01.899 --> 00:40:02.733
Hey.

00:40:04.402 --> 00:40:05.276
Hey!

00:40:05.277 --> 00:40:06.862
ELECTRONICS ENGINEERING LEE KANG

00:40:23.712 --> 00:40:27.716
GUEST LECTURE WITH AUTHOR KIM SU-HUN

00:40:29.051 --> 00:40:30.970
AUTHOR OF EYES OF THE HOUSE

00:41:08.799 --> 00:41:09.842
Hey, Professor Park.

00:41:10.342 --> 00:41:11.927
<i>Hey, Mun-oh! I mean...</i>

00:41:12.428 --> 00:41:14.680
<i>Professor Heo, where are you?</i>

00:41:15.347 --> 00:41:16.306
Well...

00:41:16.307 --> 00:41:18.976
<i>Mr. Kim is already here waiting for you.</i>

00:41:19.477 --> 00:41:22.103
<i>You should have a chat over coffee before the lecture.</i>

00:41:22.104 --> 00:41:23.354
Is that so?

00:41:23.355 --> 00:41:26.609
Deary me. You see, I'm on my way right now.

00:41:27.109 --> 00:41:30.153
About ten minutes? I think I'll be there in about ten.

00:41:30.154 --> 00:41:34.700
Tell him to have a cup of tea and wait a little longer, yeah?

00:41:35.201 --> 00:41:37.620
Sorry about that. I'll be there soon.

00:41:38.579 --> 00:41:39.872
Okay, see you soon.

00:41:52.134 --> 00:41:53.928
Wow, long time no see.

00:41:54.803 --> 00:41:57.805
- It's been a while. - It has indeed. Been a while.

00:41:57.806 --> 00:42:00.016
When was the last time we saw each other?

00:42:00.017 --> 00:42:02.061
Life's so busy. I can't remember...

00:42:02.561 --> 00:42:03.603
Let me see.

00:42:03.604 --> 00:42:06.857
When was it? I can't quite remember.

00:42:08.317 --> 00:42:11.027
I guess it really is nice meeting old friends.

00:42:11.028 --> 00:42:14.322
Why, I've never seen Professor Heo with such a big smile.

00:42:14.323 --> 00:42:15.783
Is that so?

00:42:17.326 --> 00:42:20.371
Yeah, I'm happy too. It's good to see you.

00:42:21.956 --> 00:42:23.165
You haven't changed.

00:42:24.041 --> 00:42:28.503
Over seven full-length novels and four short story collections,

00:42:28.504 --> 00:42:30.381
You've delved deep

00:42:31.173 --> 00:42:34.634
Into the complexity of the human psyche.

00:42:34.635 --> 00:42:37.595
But in your latest work, <i>Eyes of the House</i>,

00:42:37.596 --> 00:42:39.640
You've taken an entirely new approach

00:42:40.140 --> 00:42:42.976
By incorporating the techniques of mystery novels.

00:42:42.977 --> 00:42:43.894
That's right.

00:42:44.728 --> 00:42:46.897
I borrowed from the mystery genre.

00:42:47.523 --> 00:42:49.567
But while your standard mystery novel

00:42:50.067 --> 00:42:54.446
Focuses on solving the case, I was interested in something different.

00:42:54.947 --> 00:42:59.367
I broke every scene down into fragments, including the murder scene,

00:42:59.368 --> 00:43:02.997
And scrambled them so it's difficult to tell the sequence of events.

00:43:04.415 --> 00:43:08.252
Because what was important to me wasn't who the culprit was,

00:43:08.752 --> 00:43:10.795
Nor the resolution and conclusion of the case.

00:43:10.796 --> 00:43:15.175
It was the multi-layered human relationships surrounding it.

00:43:17.886 --> 00:43:19.013
You all got that, right?

00:43:20.431 --> 00:43:21.515
Well, I understood.

00:43:23.642 --> 00:43:26.519
Yes, it's truly remarkable.

00:43:26.520 --> 00:43:28.314
That's why most readers

00:43:29.023 --> 00:43:32.192
Have reviewed this book as "very novel" and "refreshing."

00:43:33.611 --> 00:43:36.280
But...

00:43:37.906 --> 00:43:38.991
But

00:43:40.326 --> 00:43:41.535
Some people...

00:43:45.205 --> 00:43:46.040
Some people?

00:43:47.833 --> 00:43:52.254
Well, some people say... Put differently...

00:43:54.214 --> 00:43:58.552
This may be a little uncomfortable for you to hear,

00:43:59.053 --> 00:44:02.597
But since this is a place for free discussion,

00:44:02.598 --> 00:44:03.932
I'll say it.

00:44:06.685 --> 00:44:09.605
"With this novel, Kim Su-hun is catering to the masses."

00:44:10.105 --> 00:44:14.985
Well, the fact is that there are some who hold critical opinions like this.

00:44:18.280 --> 00:44:21.991
Of course, this isn't my personal opinion.

00:44:21.992 --> 00:44:24.661
Before I came to this lecture hall today,

00:44:24.662 --> 00:44:28.207
I received a few questions from some students.

00:44:28.832 --> 00:44:30.793
This was one of the questions.

00:44:32.252 --> 00:44:33.503
Just a moment.

00:44:33.504 --> 00:44:35.172
So...

00:44:36.256 --> 00:44:39.384
Let's see.

00:44:39.385 --> 00:44:41.720
Where is it? Oh, here it is.

00:44:42.262 --> 00:44:43.639
So,

00:44:44.807 --> 00:44:47.017
This was the student's question.

00:44:48.102 --> 00:44:49.769
"Mr. Kim Su-hun,

00:44:49.770 --> 00:44:53.815
You've long established a reputation in literary fiction,

00:44:53.816 --> 00:44:58.987
So I had great respect for you and was a huge fan of yours."

00:44:59.655 --> 00:45:04.952
"But I was quite disappointed when you suddenly came out with a mystery novel."

00:45:05.452 --> 00:45:09.248
"Is it perhaps because you don't have any stories of your own left to tell

00:45:09.748 --> 00:45:14.128
That you had no choice but to cater to the masses?"

00:45:14.878 --> 00:45:16.505
That's pretty harsh.

00:45:17.464 --> 00:45:19.800
"If you don't have any stories left to tell...

00:45:21.802 --> 00:45:22.886
Wouldn't it be better

00:45:23.679 --> 00:45:28.058
To stop writing altogether?"

00:45:28.976 --> 00:45:30.102
Something like that.

00:45:31.478 --> 00:45:33.230
Which student asked this question?

00:45:41.822 --> 00:45:44.116
Is this, by any chance, your opinion, Professor Heo?

00:45:44.742 --> 00:45:46.869
What? No, it's...

00:45:47.536 --> 00:45:49.079
I'm just messing with you.

00:45:49.705 --> 00:45:52.457
I'd like to thank the fan who asked this, whoever you are.

00:45:52.458 --> 00:45:57.004
Sounds like you're very interested in me and have followed my work for a long time.

00:45:57.504 --> 00:45:59.089
To answer your question,

00:45:59.715 --> 00:46:02.009
Yes, you're right. Catering to the masses.

00:46:03.761 --> 00:46:06.637
The verb "to cater to" could be interpreted two ways.

00:46:06.638 --> 00:46:10.726
"To satisfy the desires or needs of the general public."

00:46:11.310 --> 00:46:13.519
That can be interpreted negatively as pandering,

00:46:13.520 --> 00:46:15.105
But it could be a positive.

00:46:15.856 --> 00:46:17.357
"Finding common ground."

00:46:17.858 --> 00:46:20.569
According to that second definition,

00:46:21.069 --> 00:46:22.946
It is essential to cater to all in art.

00:46:23.489 --> 00:46:26.824
What could be more exciting than the author and the readers

00:46:26.825 --> 00:46:29.286
Finding common ground?

00:46:31.038 --> 00:46:34.625
What truly matters is not "what" but always "how."

00:46:35.209 --> 00:46:37.961
A flexible and multi-faceted perspective is crucial.

00:46:38.921 --> 00:46:41.589
If you insist on sticking to a world you're familiar with,

00:46:41.590 --> 00:46:43.759
Your creativity will inevitably wither.

00:46:44.635 --> 00:46:48.429
That is why I will continue to tell new stories, experiment with new forms,

00:46:48.430 --> 00:46:52.267
And strive to become even better at catering to the masses.

00:47:05.197 --> 00:47:07.532
The atmosphere was great today, wasn't it?

00:47:07.533 --> 00:47:10.576
- The students' response was just... - It was amazing.

00:47:10.577 --> 00:47:11.829
- Mr. Kim. - Thanks.

00:47:12.329 --> 00:47:16.249
Of all the events we've organized so far, today's had the highest attendance.

00:47:16.250 --> 00:47:18.710
The dean was so excited.

00:47:19.461 --> 00:47:21.796
Thanks to you, I got a lot of compliments today.

00:47:21.797 --> 00:47:26.969
Oh, please. It's all thanks to you and Professor Heo, who hosted.

00:47:27.845 --> 00:47:31.430
But more than anything, the students were listening so intently,

00:47:31.431 --> 00:47:33.891
I got very excited and talked way more than usual.

00:47:33.892 --> 00:47:36.894
- Thank you. - The students really were great today.

00:47:36.895 --> 00:47:39.064
Why don't they act like that in my lectures?

00:47:39.565 --> 00:47:40.982
You just have to do better.

00:47:40.983 --> 00:47:43.025
Let's have a drink. It's an honor.

00:47:43.026 --> 00:47:43.943
Yes.

00:47:43.944 --> 00:47:46.029
- Lovely to meet you. - Truly an honor.

00:47:53.829 --> 00:47:56.790
Why have you been so quiet, Professor Heo?

00:47:57.749 --> 00:48:01.586
Not at all. I've just been listening and enjoying your conversation.

00:48:01.587 --> 00:48:03.713
Right. You two are friends, aren't you?

00:48:03.714 --> 00:48:05.382
Yes, from university.

00:48:07.301 --> 00:48:08.552
Do you enjoy teaching?

00:48:10.345 --> 00:48:12.222
How could it possibly be fun?

00:48:13.307 --> 00:48:18.895
Mr. Kim, your daughter's pen name is Lee I-pil, isn't it?

00:48:18.896 --> 00:48:22.231
She made her debut last year with <i>Seventeen Green Wings</i>.

00:48:22.232 --> 00:48:23.691
Wow, really?

00:48:23.692 --> 00:48:26.736
That writer who made a clean sweep of the literary debut awards

00:48:26.737 --> 00:48:29.071
Was your daughter? Wow.

00:48:29.072 --> 00:48:30.823
I think I've heard about it too.

00:48:30.824 --> 00:48:33.910
I guess there are no secrets in this world.

00:48:33.911 --> 00:48:37.079
I even came up with her pen name so people wouldn't know.

00:48:37.080 --> 00:48:39.665
Wow, how impressive.

00:48:39.666 --> 00:48:42.126
I guess literary talent runs in the family.

00:48:42.127 --> 00:48:44.504
You must be so proud. I'm so jealous.

00:48:45.380 --> 00:48:50.218
A talented child <i>and</i> your career? You really do have it all.

00:49:47.275 --> 00:49:48.276
Mr. Heo.

00:49:49.820 --> 00:49:50.904
What are you...

00:49:54.950 --> 00:49:55.867
You work here?

00:49:56.618 --> 00:49:57.452
Yes.

00:49:59.037 --> 00:50:00.831
You must be here with someone.

00:50:01.832 --> 00:50:02.791
Yeah.

00:50:04.334 --> 00:50:06.503
What were you scribbling while working?

00:50:11.591 --> 00:50:12.467
This is just...

00:50:13.552 --> 00:50:16.430
Just what, punk? You don't even turn in your assignments.

00:50:20.308 --> 00:50:21.685
Actually, I was thinking...

00:50:23.979 --> 00:50:25.981
Of applying to a writing contest.

00:50:26.606 --> 00:50:28.275
Literary debut awards.

00:50:29.151 --> 00:50:32.320
I heard the prize money can be decent, so I thought I'd give it a shot.

00:50:32.904 --> 00:50:34.322
What, a contest?

00:50:35.240 --> 00:50:36.825
Mr. Heo, you told me

00:50:38.243 --> 00:50:39.411
That I have talent.

00:50:41.830 --> 00:50:45.500
<i>But I haven't found a story that I want to write just yet.</i>

00:51:03.643 --> 00:51:05.729
Literary debut awards.

00:51:10.108 --> 00:51:11.735
That rascal.

00:51:15.947 --> 00:51:17.991
What a load of crap.

00:51:25.791 --> 00:51:27.209
{\an8}LITERARY DEBUT AWARD LEE KANG

00:51:28.418 --> 00:51:30.837
Thank you. Thank you so much.

00:51:33.507 --> 00:51:36.760
But this award truly belongs

00:51:37.427 --> 00:51:38.719
To someone else.

00:51:38.720 --> 00:51:40.472
"You have talent."

00:51:40.972 --> 00:51:43.517
The person who opened my eyes with those words.

00:51:44.351 --> 00:51:45.811
The person who taught me

00:51:46.311 --> 00:51:49.481
What literature is, and beyond that, what it means to live.

00:51:53.443 --> 00:51:54.694
My mentor, Mr. Heo Mun-oh.

00:51:57.948 --> 00:51:59.491
Thank you so much.

00:53:00.886 --> 00:53:01.928
Hey.

00:53:03.555 --> 00:53:07.309
Do you think the literary debut awards are child's play?

00:53:09.019 --> 00:53:11.646
You don't stand a chance with your skills, you punk.

00:53:24.868 --> 00:53:25.869
Then...

00:53:28.663 --> 00:53:31.248
If you have them,

00:53:31.249 --> 00:53:34.878
The problems for that competition or whatever...

00:53:38.715 --> 00:53:41.468
Will you start taking writing seriously?

00:53:44.179 --> 00:53:46.097
And take the literature lessons again?

00:53:58.818 --> 00:53:59.653
Then, kid,

00:54:00.403 --> 00:54:03.448
What do I need to do? Tell me!

00:54:15.210 --> 00:54:16.962
Are you sure you're okay with this?

00:54:18.296 --> 00:54:21.383
<i>It's actually pretty simple. You just need to do as I say.</i>

00:54:21.883 --> 00:54:23.926
<i>Yeah, well, what do I need to do exactly?</i>

00:54:23.927 --> 00:54:26.346
<i>Go to Professor Park Hyeong-jong's office.</i>

00:54:27.013 --> 00:54:28.098
<i>Park Hyeong-jong?</i>

00:54:28.848 --> 00:54:30.766
<i>- Professor Park from Engineering? - Yes.</i>

00:54:30.767 --> 00:54:33.770
<i>He's head of the competition's problem selection committee.</i>

00:54:34.980 --> 00:54:37.440
<i>That guy just needs to have his fingers in every pie.</i>

00:54:38.024 --> 00:54:41.695
<i>Wait. How did you know that I'm acquainted with Professor Park?</i>

00:54:42.279 --> 00:54:44.446
<i>Do you think I'd have asked otherwise?</i>

00:54:44.447 --> 00:54:46.449
<i>I've seen you two talking before.</i>

00:54:46.950 --> 00:54:48.158
- Enjoy your meal. - Yeah.

00:54:48.159 --> 00:54:49.244
Eat up.

00:54:49.869 --> 00:54:51.746
- Here you are. - Thank you.

00:54:55.375 --> 00:54:57.544
- Enjoy your meal. - You too.

00:55:01.339 --> 00:55:02.299
Professor Park.

00:55:03.466 --> 00:55:05.260
Mun-oh! Come join me.

00:55:06.011 --> 00:55:07.970
- You're eating quite late. - As are you.

00:55:07.971 --> 00:55:11.515
<i>And after I'm in Professor Park's office? What do I do once I'm there?</i>

00:55:11.516 --> 00:55:12.433
This is nice.

00:55:12.434 --> 00:55:16.770
<i>The competition is tomorrow, so the problems will be on his computer.</i>

00:55:16.771 --> 00:55:19.898
<i>All you need to do is copy them onto a USB drive. Simple, right?</i>

00:55:19.899 --> 00:55:23.320
<i>Punk, you call that simple? How would I get into his computer?</i>

00:55:23.820 --> 00:55:25.487
<i>I'd need to know his password!</i>

00:55:25.488 --> 00:55:29.909
<i>Right, that's why Professor Park needs to unlock it himself.</i>

00:55:33.496 --> 00:55:34.331
Professor Park.

00:55:36.708 --> 00:55:40.170
I have a favor to ask.

00:55:40.795 --> 00:55:43.548
Wow, you've never asked for a favor before.

00:55:44.716 --> 00:55:45.799
Go ahead.

00:55:45.800 --> 00:55:47.468
It's just that

00:55:47.469 --> 00:55:52.348
I was thinking it's about time I updated the way I take attendance.

00:55:52.349 --> 00:55:53.557
- Really? - Yes.

00:55:53.558 --> 00:55:56.060
You told me about it once before.

00:55:56.061 --> 00:55:58.521
Wow, this is music to my ears.

00:55:59.022 --> 00:56:01.440
Yeah, it's about time you updated it.

00:56:01.441 --> 00:56:04.860
Okay, I'll go to your office tomorrow and install it for you.

00:56:04.861 --> 00:56:06.404
No, not my office.

00:56:07.322 --> 00:56:10.157
I'd like to do it at your office.

00:56:10.158 --> 00:56:15.205
Shouldn't I at least see how it's run first?

00:56:16.998 --> 00:56:17.831
Really?

00:56:17.832 --> 00:56:21.543
I don't really have time today, so come to my office tomorrow.

00:56:21.544 --> 00:56:23.213
- I'll show you. - Tomorrow?

00:56:23.713 --> 00:56:26.174
No, tomorrow's too late. It has to be done today.

00:56:28.134 --> 00:56:32.389
I have something to attend to tomorrow, so I'll be a bit busy.

00:56:33.264 --> 00:56:35.934
Can't I just stop by for a bit today?

00:56:36.518 --> 00:56:38.853
- Today? Now? - Yeah, it won't take long.

00:56:39.437 --> 00:56:41.772
Okay, well, I have a little time to spare.

00:56:41.773 --> 00:56:44.733
- Let's go, then. - Okay. Let's swing by now, then.

00:56:44.734 --> 00:56:46.902
- Strike while the iron is hot. - Now?

00:56:46.903 --> 00:56:49.196
Yeah, just for a bit. This food is terrible.

00:56:49.197 --> 00:56:50.406
I barely ate anything.

00:56:50.407 --> 00:56:53.242
It's terrible. I'll treat you to some duck later.

00:56:53.243 --> 00:56:54.160
But...

00:56:54.661 --> 00:56:56.078
- Let's go, okay? - But this food...

00:56:56.079 --> 00:56:57.454
- Come on. - TA Kim.

00:56:57.455 --> 00:56:58.914
- Yes? - Our trays, please.

00:56:58.915 --> 00:57:00.040
- Sure. - Sorry.

00:57:00.041 --> 00:57:01.625
- Sorry. - Goodbye.

00:57:01.626 --> 00:57:03.877
I blathered on for about 30 minutes, I think?

00:57:03.878 --> 00:57:07.465
But when the show aired, I was only on for about a minute or two.

00:57:07.966 --> 00:57:12.429
And after coming all the way to my office and begging me to do it.

00:57:14.013 --> 00:57:15.765
It's truly convenient.

00:57:16.266 --> 00:57:18.017
- Hello. - Hi, Mi-jin.

00:57:18.560 --> 00:57:20.144
<i>No, I can't do it.</i>

00:57:20.145 --> 00:57:22.271
<i>I just don't think I can do it.</i>

00:57:22.272 --> 00:57:25.482
<i>How could I, an educator, do such a thing?</i>

00:57:25.483 --> 00:57:27.485
<i>It's too late to say that now.</i>

00:57:30.155 --> 00:57:32.115
Mun-oh, are you feeling unwell?

00:57:33.908 --> 00:57:35.952
Professor Park.

00:57:36.619 --> 00:57:39.664
I'm sorry, but I need to go to the bathroom quickly.

00:57:40.206 --> 00:57:42.458
All right. Be back soon.

00:57:42.459 --> 00:57:43.667
- Okay. - I'll be inside.

00:57:43.668 --> 00:57:45.003
Yeah, sorry about that.

00:57:59.809 --> 00:58:01.644
<i>There's no need to feel guilty.</i>

00:58:02.145 --> 00:58:04.605
<i>I'm not going to participate in the finals anyway,</i>

00:58:04.606 --> 00:58:07.066
<i>so we wouldn't be hurting anybody.</i>

00:58:13.406 --> 00:58:16.993
Hit this, and I'll log in with my account first.

00:58:17.744 --> 00:58:19.078
Once you're logged in...

00:58:19.954 --> 00:58:21.289
<i>The problem is,</i>

00:58:21.789 --> 00:58:24.249
<i>I'm not sure how we could get him</i>

00:58:24.250 --> 00:58:25.417
<i>out of his office.</i>

00:58:25.418 --> 00:58:26.544
<i>For that,</i>

00:58:27.545 --> 00:58:28.837
<i>I've come up with a plan.</i>

00:58:28.838 --> 00:58:29.756
<i>What?</i>

00:58:30.256 --> 00:58:31.924
<i>You have? What is it?</i>

00:58:31.925 --> 00:58:36.262
...the attendance scores will automatically be added to the final...

00:58:37.514 --> 00:58:39.474
- What's wrong? - My chest.

00:58:39.974 --> 00:58:42.894
- It's coming. - Mun-oh, what's wrong?

00:58:43.520 --> 00:58:44.811
I feel it coming.

00:58:44.812 --> 00:58:45.730
What...

00:58:46.231 --> 00:58:47.981
Are you okay? Should I call 911?

00:58:47.982 --> 00:58:50.776
No, you don't have to call them.

00:58:50.777 --> 00:58:52.654
- But... - Just give me a minute.

00:58:54.113 --> 00:58:55.155
What is it?

00:58:55.156 --> 00:58:57.534
My meds must be in my car.

00:58:58.034 --> 00:58:59.785
Hey, what meds?

00:58:59.786 --> 00:59:01.079
For my angina.

00:59:01.663 --> 00:59:03.539
Mun-oh, you have angina?

00:59:03.540 --> 00:59:05.290
Okay, just wait here a minute.

00:59:05.291 --> 00:59:06.291
I'm so sorry.

00:59:06.292 --> 00:59:08.085
- Just wait here. - I'm sorry.

00:59:08.086 --> 00:59:09.128
I'll be right back!

00:59:09.921 --> 00:59:11.631
- Hello, Professor. - Hey, yeah.

00:59:25.520 --> 00:59:27.897
<i>- What medicine is it? - You don't need to know, punk.</i>

00:59:29.482 --> 00:59:30.567
<i>It's for hemorrhoids.</i>

00:59:36.197 --> 00:59:37.489
Oh man, come on.

00:59:37.490 --> 00:59:38.658
Damn it!

00:59:40.243 --> 00:59:44.454
<i>But the parking lot is too close. It won't take him more than five minutes.</i>

00:59:44.455 --> 00:59:45.915
<i>Five minutes is plenty.</i>

00:59:46.416 --> 00:59:47.792
<i>Just tell me the file name.</i>

00:59:48.793 --> 00:59:52.004
<i>The thing is, I don't know what the file name would be.</i>

00:59:52.005 --> 00:59:52.922
<i>What?</i>

00:59:53.673 --> 00:59:55.133
<i>You damn punk!</i>

01:00:13.109 --> 01:00:15.570
<i>You're going to end up making me ill.</i>

01:00:20.199 --> 01:00:21.618
Damn it, where is it?

01:00:24.746 --> 01:00:25.705
Let's see.

01:00:39.344 --> 01:00:40.761
Oh, here it is!

01:00:40.762 --> 01:00:42.929
YEONSEO UNIVERSITY PROGRAMMING COMPETITION

01:00:42.930 --> 01:00:44.265
ANSWERS COMPETITION PROBLEMS

01:00:44.766 --> 01:00:46.142
- Hello. - Yeah.

01:00:48.394 --> 01:00:49.896
Hey, yeah.

01:01:10.833 --> 01:01:11.834
Got it.

01:01:12.585 --> 01:01:13.544
It's done.

01:01:19.133 --> 01:01:20.343
Damn it.

01:01:24.472 --> 01:01:26.349
Why is it so slow?

01:01:28.017 --> 01:01:29.143
50%.

01:01:30.436 --> 01:01:32.188
Come on, hurry.

01:01:35.817 --> 01:01:37.776
Okay. Almost there.

01:01:37.777 --> 01:01:39.612
Hurry.

01:01:44.117 --> 01:01:45.576
Just a little more.

01:01:51.958 --> 01:01:53.251
Mun-oh, your meds.

01:01:53.835 --> 01:01:54.793
Right.

01:01:54.794 --> 01:01:55.795
Are you okay?

01:01:58.089 --> 01:02:00.006
- Are you okay? - Thanks, Professor Park.

01:02:00.007 --> 01:02:02.634
I feel much better, thanks to you.

01:02:02.635 --> 01:02:05.846
You see, it just swoops in.

01:02:05.847 --> 01:02:08.182
- Yes? - Then it flies away.

01:02:09.308 --> 01:02:10.392
Sorry for the bother.

01:02:10.393 --> 01:02:11.309
No, it's...

01:02:11.310 --> 01:02:13.145
Oh, and Professor Park.

01:02:13.146 --> 01:02:15.981
I thought about it,

01:02:15.982 --> 01:02:18.568
And maybe my way is better after all.

01:02:19.068 --> 01:02:19.901
Sorry?

01:02:19.902 --> 01:02:21.571
- Thanks anyway. - Yeah.

01:02:22.071 --> 01:02:23.531
- Are you sure you're okay? - Yeah.

01:02:24.699 --> 01:02:26.200
But how are you suddenly fine?

01:02:31.914 --> 01:02:33.291
Sheesh, that scared me.

01:02:35.209 --> 01:02:36.085
Damn.

01:02:36.711 --> 01:02:37.545
I'm beat.

01:02:48.556 --> 01:02:50.683
- Hello, Professor. - Yeah.

01:03:09.577 --> 01:03:10.577
Hello.

01:03:10.578 --> 01:03:12.330
Hello, Professor.

01:03:21.339 --> 01:03:23.466
Professor! Hello.

01:05:01.480 --> 01:05:03.357
Mun-oh. Heo Mun-oh.

01:05:03.858 --> 01:05:05.234
You've lost it.

01:05:05.735 --> 01:05:07.028
Totally lost the plot.

01:05:12.742 --> 01:05:16.120
Mun-oh, what are you even doing?

01:05:17.538 --> 01:05:20.499
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

01:07:46.645 --> 01:07:51.650
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

